p-content/uploads/2024/09/how-to-make-a-london-fog-drink-60x60.jpg 60w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/how-to-make-a-london-fog-drink-750x750.jpg 750w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/how-to-make-a-london-fog-drink-730x730.jpg 730w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/how-to-make-a-london-fog-drink-700x700.jpg 700w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/how-to-make-a-london-fog-drink-550x550.jpg 550w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/how-to-make-a-london-fog-drink-156x156.jpg 156w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/how-to-make-a-london-fog-drink-288x288.jpg 288w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/how-to-make-a-london-fog-drink-500x500.jpg 500w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/how-to-make-a-london-fog-drink.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"h-london-fog-tea-latte-variations\"\u003eLondon Fog Tea Latte Variations\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eChoice of Tea\u003c/strong\u003e – Substitute Earl Grey for another black tea or, if looking to avoid caffeine, an herbal tea. You can also find decaffeinated Earl Grey tea.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eChoice of Milk\u003c/strong\u003e – You can use any kind of milk or milk alternative you prefer. While I typically use whole or 2% milk in latte recipes, you could use oat milk, soy milk, almond milk, etc.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFlavor Variations\u003c/strong\u003e – While many add lavender to a London Fog, it’s optional. You could also choose to add other flavors like \u003ca href=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/mint-simple-syrup/\"\u003emint simple syrup\u003c/a\u003e or \u003ca href=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/try-this-rosemary-latte/\"\u003erosemary simple syrup\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ci